          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When rendering materials with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnlightingmodelphysicallybased"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " lighting model, SceneKit illuminates surfaces differently according to the environment that surrounds them. For example, with physically based shading, even a diffuse surface takes on some color from the sky above it and the ground below it."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "For realistic results, reuse the same contents for both the lighting environment and the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnscene/1523665-background"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " property."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "tip"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
